.TH "HTMLIMAGEELEMENT.ALT" "3JS" "November 7, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLImageElement.alt \- HTMLImageElement: alt property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]alt\f[B]\f[R] property of the \f[CR]HTMLImageElement\f[R]
interface provides fallback (alternate) text to display when the image
specified by the \f[CR]<img>\f[R] element is not displayed, whether
because of an error, because the user has disabled the loading of
images, or because the image hasn\(cqt finished loading yet.
It reflects the \f[CR]<img>\f[R] element\(cqs \f[CR]alt\f[R] content
attribute.
.PP
There are important accessibility implications of providing appropriate
alt text, and the requirements may differ based on the purpose of the
image.
See the HTML \f[CR]<img>\f[R] reference for more information.
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Setting the alt attribute
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] img = \f[B]new\f[R] Image();
img.src = \(dqexample.png\(dq;
img.alt = \(dqAn example picture\(dq;
.EE
